Detailed Description

This is a dumb filter class.

It uses only the first element of auxFiltered. It simply sets the position to the last input position. It does however ensure ordering on time, and doesn't call the Entity's 'pos' function unless necessary. This could almost be the Teleport filter.

bool DumbFilter::getLastInput ( double &  time,
SpaceID &  spaceID,
EntityID &  vehicleID,
Position3D &  pos,
Vector3 &  posError,
float *  auxFiltered 
) [virtual]

This function gets the last input received by the filter.

Its arguments will be untouched if no input has yet been received.

Parameters:
time Will be set to the time stamp of the last input.
spaceID Will be set to the space ID of the last input.
vehicleID Will be set to the vehicle ID provided in the last input.
pos The position of received in the last input, with its height fully resolved.
posError The amount of uncertainty in the position.
auxFiltered An pointer to a float into which the yaw of the last input will be placed.
Returns:
Returns true if an input existed and the values in the parameters were set.

Implements Filter.

void DumbFilter::input ( double  time,
SpaceID  spaceID,
EntityID  vehicleID,
const Position3D &  pos,
const Vector3 &  posError,
float *  auxFiltered 
) [virtual]

This method updates the stored position and direction information with that provided.

But only it the new data's time stamp if more recent.

Parameters:
time The estimated client time when the input was sent from the server.
spaceID The server space that the position resides in.
vehicleID The ID of the vehicle in who's coordinate system the position is defined. A null vehicle ID means that the position is in world coordinates.
pos The new position in either local vehicle or world space/common coordinates. The player relative compression will have already been decoded at this point by the network layer.
posError The amount of uncertainty in the position.
auxFiltered If not NULL, a pointer to a float containing a new yaw.

void DumbFilter::output ( double  time  )  [virtual]

This method updates the slave entity's position, velocity and yaw to match that stored from the last input.

Parameters:
time The client game time in seconds that the entity's volatile members should be updated for.
